plot: John gives a brief update on 'Stupid Watergate II' and then dives into the main topic - the trouble with voting machines.

First, in 'Stupid Watergate II' news, Trump attacks the latest Impeachment witness, U.S. Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman, and releases new anti-Impeachment t-shirts based on the movie Hocus Pocus (1993). Then, John dives into the main topic - the trouble with voting machines. Many have outdated software, which makes them vulnerable to hacking, others can easily be tampered with physically to alter the results, and those that do not use any form of paper trail make checking their accuracy impossible. Also, MSNBC's Nicolle Wallace has a bleeping problem with Trump, and local news dress up their anchors for Halloween.—Niaz Islam Arif
